意大利版“火神山”要来了。
The Italian version of Mount Fire is coming.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 南博一医生在布雷西亚诊所门诊检测新冠肺炎疑似患者。
Pang Pai reporter Dr. Nan Bo Yi at the Brescia Clinic clinic to test suspected patients with new crown pneumonia.
意大利媒体报道称，该国新冠肺炎疫情最严重的伦巴第大区正考虑把米兰国际展览中心（Fiera Milano City）改造成一个可容纳600个床位的大型医院，这种医院类似于中国武汉建成的“火神山”医院。
Italy's Lombardy region, which has the worst outbreak of pneumonia in the country, is considering transforming the Fiera Milano City into a large 600-bed hospital similar to the one built in Wuhan, China, according to Italian media.
据意大利《晚邮报》（Corriere Della Sera）3月11日报道，这座占地12000平方米的米兰国际展览中心计划被改造成20个医疗单位，每个单位设30个重症监护床位，整个中心将安装空气过滤系统。
The 12,000-square-metre Milan International Exhibition Center will be converted into 20 medical units, each with 30 intensive-care beds, and an air-filtration system will be installed, Corriere della Sera reported Wednesday.
《晚邮报》形容这种医院为“武汉式”医院。
The Evening Post described the hospital as Wuhan-style.
但是，中心的改造还需要政府提供必要的设备，包括呼吸机、重症监控系统和其他医疗辅助设备。
However, the rehabilitation of the centre will also require the Government to provide the necessary equipment, including respirators, critical care systems and other medical aids.
此外，还需要更多医护人员。
In addition, there is a need for more medical personnel.
按照需求，每8名患者需要配置一名医生，每3名患者需要配备一名护士，并根据情况配备警卫。
There is a need for one doctor for every eight patients and one nurse for every three patients, with guards as appropriate.
因此，总共需要450至500名医生和1200至1300名护士。
Thus, a total of 450 to 500 doctors and 1,200 to 1,300 nurses are required.
另据德国《明镜周刊》国际版11日报道，伦巴第高级卫生官员朱利奥·加莱拉（Giulio Gallera）表示，伦巴第政府目前正认真考虑在米兰国际展览中心设置床位，或是建立集装箱病房收治病人。
Giulio Gallera, a senior health official in Lombardy, said the Lombardy government was seriously considering opening a bed at the Milan International Exhibition Center or setting up a container ward to house patients, Der Spiegel reported Wednesday.
伦巴第大区是整个意大利的疫源地和重灾区。
Lombardy is the epicentre and disaster area of the whole of Italy.
截至3月10日，在整个伦巴第大区共有5791例新冠肺炎确诊病例，另有135例死亡病例，各医院的重症监护病房共收治有466名患者。
As at 10 March, there had been 5,791 confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia and 135 deaths throughout the Lombardy region, with 466 patients admitted to intensive care units in hospitals.
加莱拉表示，在短短两周内，伦巴第卫生部门已经增设了223个重症监护床位，并计划再增加150个床位，但是需求仍在持续增长。
In just two weeks, Lombardy's health department has added 223 intensive care beds and plans to add another 150 beds, but demand continues to grow, Mr. Gallera said.
他预计这种状况还需持续两到三周。
He expects the situation to continue for another two to three weeks.
